id: pm-1lef
title: Opt CI JavaScript actions into Node 24 runtime
description: GitHub Actions run 26000939754 was green but emitted Node 20 JavaScript action deprecation annotations for actions/download-artifact. Opt the CI workflow into the Node 24 JavaScript action runtime using the documented environment knob and add workflow contract coverage so future CI stays warning-clean on free GitHub runners.
type: Chore
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[4]: ci,free-tier,github-actions,node24
created_at: "2026-05-17T19:55:48.113Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T20:04:30.707Z"
assignee: codex-extensive-audit-2026-05-17
author: codex-extensive-audit-2026-05-17
acceptance_criteria: CI workflow sets FORCE_JAVASCRIPT_ACTIONS_TO_NODE24=true; workflow contract tests assert the setting; local focused workflow contract test passes; pushed GitHub Actions CI is green without the prior Node 20 action deprecation annotation.
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-17T19:55:48.113Z",codex-extensive-audit-2026-05-17,"Duplicate check: searched pm for 'Node.js 20 actions deprecated download-artifact GitHub Actions'. Existing hits pm-hfny and pm-tzwy are closed historical action pinning/performance work; no open item owns the current run 26000939754 Node 20 action runtime annotation, so this chore is net-new under pm-rnpb."
  "2026-05-17T19:56:34.903Z",codex-extensive-audit-2026-05-17,"Evidence: added workflow-level FORCE_JAVASCRIPT_ACTIONS_TO_NODE24=true in .github/workflows/ci.yml and added ci-workflow-contract coverage for the setting. Linked pm test passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts (4 tests, 1 file)."
  "2026-05-17T20:04:26.059Z",codex-extensive-audit-2026-05-17,"Follow-up evidence: run 26001127637 was green but still emitted forced-runtime annotations because actions/download-artifact v5 declares node20. Upstream actions/download-artifact v8.0.1 resolves tag v8.0.1/v8 to SHA 3e5f45b2cfb9172054b4087a40e8e0b5a5461e7c and action.yml declares runs.using=node24, so CI now pins that SHA and the contract asserts the v8.0.1 reference."
